  "prompt": "How do I study in college?",
  "response": "Here are some effective study strategies for college:\n\n1. Time Management\n- Create a study schedule\n- Use a planner or digital calendar\n- Break large tasks into smaller steps\n- Prioritize assignments\n\n2. Study Techniques\n- Take good notes in class\n- Review notes regularly\n- Use active reading strategies\n- Highlight and summarize key information\n- Create study guides\n- Use flashcards\n- Practice past exams\n\n3. Study Environment\n- Find a quiet, comfortable space\n- Minimize distractions\n- Use library or study rooms\n- Have good lighting and comfortable seating\n\n4. Learning Strategies\n- Attend all classes\n- Participate in class discussions\n- Form study groups\n- Ask professors for help\n- Utilize office hours\n- Use campus tutoring resources\n\n5. Healthy Habits\n- Get enough sleep\n- Eat nutritious meals\n- Exercise regularly\n- Manage stress\n- Take breaks while studying\n\n6. Technology Tools\n- Use study apps\n- Digital flashcard programs\n- Online research databases\n- Note-taking apps\n\n7. Exam Preparation\n- Start studying early\n- Practice practice practice\n- Get enough rest before exams\n- Stay calm and confident\n\nRemember, everyone learns differently, so experiment to find what works best for you.",
